\ Frame round-trip through a binary image (save-image / load-image).
\ Build a nested frame mixing a sub-frame and a set, save it (it stays on
\ the data stack), clear live state, restore from the image, and verify the
\ whole structure — including nested frame and set — came back.

{ :a 1 :b { :c 2 } :d < 7 8 > } "/tmp/lf-test-68.image" save-image
clear
"/tmp/lf-test-68.image" load-image

dup /a @ . cr        \ 1
dup /b/c @ . cr      \ 2   nested frame survived
dup /d @ size . cr   \ 2   nested set survived
. cr                 \ the whole restored frame
